data.name: HelpMenu
data.value:
USAGE: netlenium [OPTIONS] (main server)
OPTIONS: -h, --help Displays the help menu and exits
--disable-stdout Disables standard output
--disable-file-logging Disables logging to files
--driver-logging-level [0-3] Logging level for Driver Sessions 0 = Silent 1 = Information, Warning & Errors (Default) 2 = Verbose 3 = Debugging
--server-logging-level [0-3] Logging level for the Web Service 0 = Silent 1 = Information, Warning & Errors (Default) 2 = Verbose 3 = Debugging
-p, --port [Default: 6410] The port to run the Web Service on
--server-name [Default: 'Netlenium Server'] Optional custom name for this server
--max-sessions [Default: 100] The max amount of sessions that are allowed to be created
--session-inactivity-limit [Default: 10] The amount of minutes that a session is allowed to be inactive before it gets closed. Using 0 as the value will never close inactive session
--disable-chrome-driver Disables the ability to start Chrome Drivers
--disable-firefox-driver Disables the ability to start Firefox Drivers
--auth-password [Optional] Authentication Password for Web Service access
